    "body": "This is most likely already available.\n\nBy network change, do you mean whenever there is a new block (or a new unconfirmed transaction?) In web3.js, you can use one form of [web3.eth.filter](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JavaScript-API#web3ethfilter) to fire a callback.\n\nMonitoring a specific address or contract is more difficult. If it's a contract, you can write it to log when something specific happened (i.e. a deposit is made) and then listen in web3.js with [events in the contract object](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JavaScript-API#contract-events).\n",
