    "body": "I'm not sure how web3 would, theoretically speaking, even know about a change in nodes _without_ manually polling. AFAIK, the JSON-RPC is usually just a fancy HTTP POST to the node. There's not a connection _per se_, only that a given web3 object is set to interact with a given node.\n\nThere's work on pub/sub in various places, which would allow for this. (If nothing else, because all the subscriptions stop working!)\n",
